Feature: Users Listing

  Scenario: Display users in table format
    Given Users exist in the system
    When User navigates to users listing page
    Then Users table displays with expected columns

  Scenario: Show empty state when no users
    Given No users are registered
    When User navigates to users listing page
    Then Message "No hay usuarios registrados" is displayed

  Scenario: Edit user via modal dialog
    Given Users exist in the system
    When User clicks edit action for a user
    Then Edit modal dialog opens
    When User updates fields and saves
    Then HTTP PUT /api/users/:id succeeds with 200

  Scenario: Cancel edit operation
    Given Edit modal is open
    When User clicks "Cancelar" button
    Then Modal closes without saving

  Scenario: Delete user
    Given Users exist in the system
    When User clicks delete action for a user
    Then HTTP DELETE /api/users/:id succeeds

  Scenario: Navigation from users listing
    Given User is on users listing page
    When User clicks "Registro" link
    Then User navigates to registration form page